{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1811f834-721b-41c3-84de-6eedf1385a02","content":"Here's what to do:\n\n1. **Remove** the `xunit.runner.visualstudio` package reference.\n\n2. **Add** the `xunit.v3.runner.mtp` package (xUnit v3) **or**, if staying on xUnit v2, add `xunit.runner.mtp` instead:\n\n   ```xml\n   <!-- For xUnit v2 (your current version): -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n\n   <!-- OR migrate to xUnit v3: -->\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"*\" />\n   <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3.runner.mtp\" Version=\"*\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable MTP** in your project file:\n\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotNetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n   This lets `dotnet test` use MTP instead of VSTest.\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test          # works via the compatibility layer\n   dotnet run           # MTP produces an executable directly\n   ```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` (v2 bridge) lets you stay on xUnit 2.9.3 without rewriting tests.\n- If you migrate to **xUnit v3**, replace `xunit` with `xunit.v3` and update any API changes (e.g., `Assert.Equal` overloads, `TheoryData<T>` generics).\n- MTP produces a **self-contained test executable**, so `dotnet run` and direct execution work out of the box.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b703d503-2220-4b79-ac2c-ac517f08a5c0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":481,"requestId":"7689:913B3:DC1DD05:F24CA93:69F2A76A"},"id":"89f263dc-7e73-497d-bd00-ce2d26ddd4f3","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:51:00.244Z","parentId":"54a36d4d-92d3-45ea-bf9c-218d2868fb43"}
